functions.label: escapeKuery
description:
Escapes a Kuery node value to ensure that special characters, operators, and whitespace do not result in a parsing error or unintended
behavior when using the value as an argument for the `buildNode` function.

functions.label: escapeQuotes
description:
Escapes backslashes and double-quotes. (Useful when putting a string in quotes to use as a value
in a KQL expression. See the QuotedCharacter rule in kuery.peg.)

functions.label: isCCSRemoteIndexName
description:
Check whether the index expression represents a remote index (CCS) or not.
The index name is assumed to be individual index (no commas) but can contain `-`, wildcards,
datemath, remote cluster name and any other syntax permissible in index expression component.

2025/01/21 Implementation taken from https://github.com/smalyshev/elasticsearch/blob/main/server/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/transport/RemoteClusterAware.java

description: by default filters that use fields that can't be found in the specified index pattern are not applied. Set this to true if you want to apply them anyway.

children.label: nestedIgnoreUnmapped
description:
the nested field type requires a special query syntax, which includes an optional ignore_unmapped parameter that indicates whether to ignore an unmapped path and not return any documents instead of an error.
The optional ignore_unmapped parameter defaults to false.
This `nestedIgnoreUnmapped` param allows creating queries with "ignore_unmapped": true

children.label: nestedIgnoreUnmapped
description:
the Nested field type requires a special query syntax, which includes an optional ignore_unmapped parameter that indicates whether to ignore an unmapped path and not return any documents instead of an error.
The optional ignore_unmapped parameter defaults to false.
The `nestedIgnoreUnmapped` param allows creating queries with "ignore_unmapped": true

children.label: caseInsensitive
description:
Whether term-level queries should be treated as case-insensitive or not. For example, `agent.keyword: foobar` won't
match a value of "FooBar" unless this parameter is `true`.
(See https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/8.6/query-dsl-term-query.html#term-field-params)
